                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/75.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My February 11. By note received to-day Legation’s protest rejected by Haitian
                    Government on the ground that Legation not qualified to protest for a French
                    company. States French Minister here only proper person to do so. Particulars by
                    mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
